######################################################################
#
# lib Sub package 
# 
%package -n libroot
Group: ROOT
Summary: Numerical data analysis framework - shared runtime libraries
%description -n libroot
This is the shared libraries used by the ROOT system. The libraries
contain numerous C++ class definitions for various purposes, some of
which are:
    * System abstraction
    * Thin Thread API
    * Histograming
    * Persistent objects
    * GUI API
and many many others. Refer also to the class description of
root-bin.

See also root-bin package documentation for more information

More information can be obtained via the ROOT web pages:
    http://root.cern.ch

#---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Files that go into this package 
%files -n libroot -f rpm/libroot.files

#-----------------
%post -n libroot
	if ! grep -qs ^/usr/lib/root\$ /etc/ld.so.conf ; then
                echo /usr/lib/root >> /etc/ld.so.conf
        fi
	ldconfig



